==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: bilabial
<hw>bi*la"bi*al</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Linguistics)</fld>
<def>produced using both lips; -- said of a consonant. <as>As,
<ex>bilabial</ex> fricatives</as>.</def> <see>See <er>labial</er>,
<pos>adj.</pos> and <er>bilabial,</er> <pos>n.</pos></see>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bilabial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: bilabial
<hw>bi*la"bi*al</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>a
consonant that is articulated using both lips, as <examp>p</examp> or
<examp>b</examp> or <examp>w</examp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bilabiate</ent>⟦br⟧
